history.text: Hello!
have you seen the wold of wall street
Hello
I have. Solid movie.
Girlfriend didn't appreciate it, but I enjoyed it.
I agree. What would you rate it 1-10?
did she find the jokes offensive?
Probably like an 8. Yeah not her type of humor I guess.
Do you think the movie is suitable for kids under 14?
I guess that depends on your parenting style. If I was a parent, I guess I'd probably say no? But nothing wouldn't been new to me at 14. Not really sure. Interesting question. What do you think?
would've been*
I would not let children watch this movie
it also depends on maturity
Yeah, I guess I'd probably agree. I would've had to watch it at a friend
's house back then.
do you think Leonardo DiCaprio did a good job as Jordan Bellfort
Yeah I tend to like his work. I think Jonah Hill as whoever he played was great too. McConaughey as well, even though I think his part was short if I remember.
i agree, Leo did an awesome job. Jonah was my favorite actor on this cast, i feel he could have done better.
Margot Robbie was good too. I feel like this movie just came out, but it's probably been 4 years or something.
yeah the movie came out in 2013
I don't remember any other big names that were in it. Who else starred? Didn't he have a group that he ran the whole scam with?

Leonardo DiCaprio as Jordan Belfort
Jonah Hill as Donnie Azoff
 Margot Robbie as Naomi Lapaglia
● Kyle Chandler as Patrick Denham
● Rob Reiner as Max Belfort
Kyle Chandler rings a bell, but I can't place him. I'm not great at actors names. Where would you put it on a 1-10?
Do you think this movie acuratly potrays stockbrokers in this time frame?
Im not the best with names either.
I would rate it a 7-8

For all I know, it accurately portrays them now haha. I don't do much trading, so I don't interact with brokers at all. Brokers and hedge fund guys are typically portrayed that way, but I'm sure a lot of them are just doing their jobs.
yeah i think alot of the scenes were a little far-fetched

Probably. Over the top for Hollywood I guess. To be fair though, I think the guy in real life did do 
some prison time. Not sure if I have this right, but I think his buddy, played by Jonah, got involved in some sketchy enterprises in FL after he got out too.

uid1response.feedback: I've seen this movie before, but talking about it made me remember it's a pretty good one. I may have to watch it again.
